# NikCLI Documentation\n\nThis directory contains the core documentation files for NikCLI, the autonomous AI development assistant.\n\n## Current Structure\n\nThe documentation is organized as follows:\n\n- **Root Files**:\n - `introduction.mdx` - Introduction to NikCLI features and architecture\n - `ide-diagnostic-server.md` - IDE diagnostic server integration\n - `README.md` - This file\n - `ai-system.mmd` - AI system diagram\n - `ai-system.png` - AI system diagram image\n - `mint.json` - Documentation metadata\n\n- **Subdirectories**:\n - `advanced/` - Advanced topics (1 file)\n - `agent-system/` - Agent architecture (5 files)\n - `api-reference/` - API references (1 file)\n - `cli-reference/` - CLI command details (9 files)\n - `components/` - UI components documentation (20 files)\n - `contributing/` - Contribution guidelines (1 file)\n - `diagrams/` - Architecture diagrams (10 files)\n - `examples/` - Usage examples (2 files)\n - `images/` - Documentation images (3 files)\n - `logo/` - Branding assets (1 file)\n - `quickstart/` - Getting started materials (3 files)\n - `troubleshooting/` - Issue resolution (2 files)\n - `user-guide/` - User workflows (4 files)\n\n## Building and Viewing\n\nNikCLI documentation uses MDX format for rich content and is viewable in any Markdown editor or on GitHub.\n\nFor local preview with Docusaurus (if set up):\n\n`bash\n# Install dependencies\nyarn install\n\n# Start development server\nyarn docusaurus start\n`\n\n## Key Topics Covered\n\n- **Core CLI Usage**: Interactive assistant with /commands\n- **Background Agents**: Asynchronous job management with nikctl and nikd\n- **AI Integration**: Multiple providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Ollama)\n- **Tool Ecosystem**: File operations, Git, package management\n- **Security Policies**: Execution safeguards and best practices\n- **Setup and Configuration**: Environment variables and deployment\n\n## Contributing to Documentation\n\n1. **Add New Files**: Create .mdx files in appropriate subdirectories\n2. **Update Existing**: Edit content to reflect current CLI reality\n3. **Standards**:\n - Use consistent MDX formatting\n - Include code examples with `bash` or `typescript`\n - Add links to related sections\n - Keep language clear and concise\n4. **Review**: Submit PR with changes to docs/\n\nFor full contribution guidelines, see [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n## Future Plans\n\n- Expand subdirectories with detailed guides\n- Add API reference for background agents server\n- Include screenshots and diagrams\n- Integrate with documentation site generator\n\n**Note**: This documentation mirrors the current NikCLI CLI capabilities (v0.2.3). Update files as features evolve.\n","parameter name="backup">true
